<p class="eyebrow">Support / Softphone</p>
<h1>Softphone configuration.</h1>
<p class="lede">Most SIP softphones expose the same set of fields. The values are the same across vendors; only the menu paths differ.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/phone/">VoiceTel Phone (recommended)</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact/">Contact engineering</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>VoiceTel Phone is the supported path</h2>
	<p>VoiceTel ships its own web, desktop, and mobile calling apps with SIP credentials provisioned automatically through the portal. Use VoiceTel Phone unless you have a specific need for a third-party softphone (for example, integration with an existing CRM that ships a particular softphone, or a Linux desktop where VoiceTel Phone isn't available yet).</p>
	<p>The third-party softphone guides below cover configuration but won't get the same support coverage as VoiceTel Phone.</p>
</section>

